Steam is a digital distribution platform and video game company that was launched in 2003 by Valve Corporation. It allows users to purchase, download, and play video games on their computers. Steam provides a wide variety of games, including popular titles from major publishers as well as independent games created by smaller developers. In addition to selling games, Steam also provides features like social networking, matchmaking, in-game voice chat, and cloud saves. It also offers early access to games, where users can play and provide feedback to developers during the development process. Steam is available on multiple operating systems, including Windows, macOS, and Linux, and has become one of the largest digital distribution platforms for video games in the world.